Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling
optional).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste},
season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Once cooked, sprinkle with half the @grated cheese{100%g} and allow to melt,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @parsley{10%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Chimichurri Dressing ==

To make your chimichurri dressing add the parsley, half the garlic, and half
the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} to a #small bowl{}.

Add @oil{1%tbsp}, season with salt and pepper, mix together, then set aside.

== Spiced Sweetcorn ==

Drain the @sweetcorn{2%pack(s)} in a #sieve{}. Toss with the @paprika{2%sachet(s)},
a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of oil.

== Burgers ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{1%pack(s)}, remaining garlic,
2 tbsp @water{2%tbsp} and ¼ tsp @salt{¼%tsp}.

Add the @Irish beef mince{250%g}, season with pepper and mix everything
together with your hands.

Roll into evenly-sized balls then shape into 2cm thick burgers—1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place the beef burgers onto a lined baking tray.

Spread the spiced corn out on the #baking tray{} next to the burgers.

Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, sprinkle the burgers with remaining cheese, return to the oven
and allow to melt.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

== Chorizo Jam ==

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%g} until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} and allow it to evaporate
fully, then remove from the heat. Add the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet} and
mix until combined.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Cover to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

Pop the @brioche buns{2} cut-side up, into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, divide the warmed buns between plates.

Drizzle the bun lids with the chimichurri dressing.

Spread the chorizo jam over the bun bases, then top with the burgers. Close
with the bun lids.

Serve the spiced sweetcorn and cheesy chips alongside.